{
  "texts": [
    "Human actors will likely struggle to fully grasp these workflows, which span diverse domains and physical locations.",
    "Similarly, ML alone may not suffice, as these workflows amalgamate elements of the physical world that are partially unknown, and sustainable systems will require not just prediction and experimentation, but also tool-making -with the tools themselves possessing partially unknown properties.",
    "Shown in Figure 5, a paradoxical yet intriguing possibility is conceptualizing human-in-the-loop R&D as a Massive Multiplayer Online Role-Playing Game (MMORPG).",
    "In this framework, activities like magic, forging, and potion making symbolize real-world processes in physics, engineering, and chemistry, with AI acting as an advanced intermediary, connecting humans to remote-controlled and automated research and manufacturing tools.",
    "overseeing these automated systems."
  ]
}